ence is brought to bear, both from the laboratory and from field studies, the book is not burdened with excessive detail. The writing is crisp, and the references are tailored to those most useful for nonspecialists. The Acoustic Sense of Animals covers a complex field with balance and clarity within a solid evolutionary framework. Equally important, it conveys the controversy and excitement that will motivate students.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aAudition (Physiologie). 0aHören. 0aPhysiologie comparée. 0aTiere (Zoologie). 0aTiere. 4aAnimal communication. 4aBioacoustics. 4aHearing -- Physiological aspects. 4aSCIENCE / Life Sciences / Biology. 4aSense organs. 7aSCIENCE / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP e-dition: Complete eBook Packagez9783110353488oZDB-23-HCO08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP e-dition: Science eBook Packagez9783110353549oZDB-23-HSP08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package Archive 1893-1999z97831104422120 cprintz978067443621340uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/harvard.978067443622040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780674436220423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780674436220/original  a978-3-11-044221-2  HUP eBook Package Archive 1893-1999c1893d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MTPY  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MTPY  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-HCO  aZDB-23-HSP